1
00:00:00,800 --> 00:00:05,300
Friday rush, Pam scans something new, a cream, no barcode.

2
00:00:05,960 --> 00:00:11,080
She names it, prises it, snaps a quick photo, sells it, 40 francs done.

3
00:00:11,980 --> 00:00:17,680
It's rough, a fast photo, no details, but the lines moving, and that's the job.

4
00:00:18,600 --> 00:00:23,460
Then Larry buys one, an hour later, Sally buys another, two in a day.

5
00:00:24,080 --> 00:00:28,700
This brand new little cream nobody has heard of on the internet.

6
00:00:29,400 --> 00:00:30,640
They know about today.

7
00:00:32,420 --> 00:00:37,820
Felix isn't in the shop, he's on the road, but he opens his phone and checks the dashboard.

8
00:00:38,260 --> 00:00:39,420
And there it is, selling.

9
00:00:39,880 --> 00:00:42,200
He knows they hit when he sees one.

10
00:00:42,380 --> 00:00:45,260
He also knows the entry is rough.

11
00:00:45,640 --> 00:00:49,180
He can't fix it from the highway, and it's not his job.

12
00:00:49,540 --> 00:00:56,900
So he sends Ralph one text, a link, the creams page on the Artemis website.

13
00:00:58,080 --> 00:01:04,340
Ralph opens that link, beautiful photos, full specs, the whole story, sitting on the website,

14
00:01:05,000 --> 00:01:07,760
a different system, not wired to the till.

15
00:01:08,680 --> 00:01:12,400
So he brings it across by hand, the real photo, the details.

16
00:01:13,080 --> 00:01:20,500
And he checks the one thing that matters, that the barcode Pam scanned really is this product.

17
00:01:21,120 --> 00:01:23,900
Because sometimes it isn't, he confirms it.

18
00:01:23,900 --> 00:01:31,800
Then he sets the cost, a reorder number, the rough little cream just grew up.

19
00:01:32,620 --> 00:01:37,700
Next morning, Pam opens the catalog, and the creams got a new face now.

20
00:01:38,840 --> 00:01:44,100
A real photo, specs that she can read straight to the customer, a margin behind it,

21
00:01:44,820 --> 00:01:47,560
a reorder that won't let it run dry.

22
00:01:48,400 --> 00:01:53,260
Here's the secret, nobody touched the 7,000 products that never sell.

23
00:01:54,020 --> 00:02:00,460
You don't polish a dead shelf, you wait for the shop to sell what's worth it.

24
00:02:00,680 --> 00:02:08,700
And it tells you in sales, a cashier born's it, a manager raises it.

25
00:02:08,880 --> 00:02:13,660
The owner just has to notice, effort follows velocity.
